patch:
diff --git a/llvm/include/llvm/IR/GenericFloatingPointPredicateUtils.h b/llvm/include/llvm/IR/GenericFloatingPointPredicateUtils.h
index 8aac9d5b49db..a01d1e41cd60 100644
--- a/llvm/include/llvm/IR/GenericFloatingPointPredicateUtils.h
+++ b/llvm/include/llvm/IR/GenericFloatingPointPredicateUtils.h
@@ -151,20 +151,44 @@ public:
       case FCmpInst::FCMP_UNO:
         return exactClass(Src, fcNan);
       case FCmpInst::FCMP_OGT: // x > 0
+        if (IsFabs)
+          // fabs(x) > 0.0 -> non-zero and not NaN (any sign)
+          return exactClass(Src, ~fcZero & ~fcNan);
         return exactClass(Src, fcPosSubnormal | fcPosNormal | fcPosInf);
       case FCmpInst::FCMP_UGT: // isnan(x) || x > 0
+        if (IsFabs)
+          // unordered greater-than: NaN or fabs(x) > 0.0 -> non-zero or NaN
+          return exactClass(Src, (~fcZero) | fcNan);
         return exactClass(Src, fcPosSubnormal | fcPosNormal | fcPosInf | fcNan);
       case FCmpInst::FCMP_OGE: // x >= 0
+        if (IsFabs)
+          // fabs(x) >= 0.0 -> !isnan(x)
+          return exactClass(Src, ~fcNan);
         return exactClass(Src, fcPositive | fcNegZero);
       case FCmpInst::FCMP_UGE: // isnan(x) || x >= 0
+        if (IsFabs)
+          // unordered greater-equal: NaN or fabs(x) >= 0.0 -> true
+          return exactClass(Src, fcAllFlags);
         return exactClass(Src, fcPositive | fcNegZero | fcNan);
       case FCmpInst::FCMP_OLT: // x < 0
+        if (IsFabs)
+          // fabs(x) < 0.0 -> false
+          return exactClass(Src, fcNone);
         return exactClass(Src, fcNegSubnormal | fcNegNormal | fcNegInf);
       case FCmpInst::FCMP_ULT: // isnan(x) || x < 0
+        if (IsFabs)
+          // unordered less-than: NaN or fabs(x) < 0.0 -> NaN only
+          return exactClass(Src, fcNan);
         return exactClass(Src, fcNegSubnormal | fcNegNormal | fcNegInf | fcNan);
       case FCmpInst::FCMP_OLE: // x <= 0
+        if (IsFabs)
+          // fabs(x) <= 0.0 -> zero and not NaN
+          return exactClass(Src, fcZero);
         return exactClass(Src, fcNegative | fcPosZero);
       case FCmpInst::FCMP_ULE: // isnan(x) || x <= 0
+        if (IsFabs)
+          // unordered less-equal: NaN or fabs(x) <= 0.0 -> zero or NaN
+          return exactClass(Src, fcZero | fcNan);
         return exactClass(Src, fcNegative | fcPosZero | fcNan);
       default:
         llvm_unreachable("all compare types are handled");

reason_thou:
1. Understanding the Issue:
The incorrect transformation removes the final fabs from "fabs(select ...)" yielding just the select result. Alive2 shows this is wrong for a negative subnormal input. InstSimplify simplified "fabs %sel" to "%sel" by concluding the sign bit of %sel is known to be zero (non-negative). That decision hinges on computeKnownFPSignBit, which relies on computeKnownFPClass on the select, which in turn uses fcmpImpliesClass to interpret the select condition "fcmp ogt (fabs x), +0.0" as filtering the result's class.

2. Analyzing opt's Log:
opt with --debug-only=instsimplify shows the pass replaced the final fabs with the select (%abs2 removed, ret %sel). This simplification occurs via InstructionSimplify::simplifyUnaryIntrinsic(), specifically:
  case Intrinsic::fabs:
    if (computeKnownFPSignBit(Op0, Q) == false)
      return Op0;
So, computeKnownFPSignBit(Op0) returned false (sign bit known zero) for Op0 = %sel.

3. Root Cause Analysis:
computeKnownFPClass for a Select tries to deduce class masks from the select condition. Our condition is "fcmp ogt fabs(x), +0.0". Semantically, ordered-greater-than of fabs(x) against +0.0 is true iff x is non-zero and not NaN. That includes negative subnormals/normals. Therefore the true branch mask must include negative classes. However, GenericFloatingPointPredicateUtils::fcmpImpliesClass mishandles this pattern when RHS is +0.0 and LHS is fabs(x). In the IsPositiveRHS path with IsFabs, it transforms class sets via inverse_fabs and then maps OGt to a ClassesGE mask that does not include negative classes, leading ValueTracking to conclude the true branch (LHS = x) is non-negative. This causes computeKnownFPSignBit to return false, and InstSimplify eliminates fabs incorrectly.

Thus, the bug is in GenericFloatingPointPredicateUtils.h: the mask computation for the case "fcmp ogt fabs(x), +0.0" must be special-cased to yield MaskIfTrue = ~fcZero & ~fcNan (all non-zero, any sign), and MaskIfFalse = fcZero | fcNan.

4. Proposed Edit Point(s):
Edit file llvm/include/llvm/IR/GenericFloatingPointPredicateUtils.h around the handling of IsPositiveRHS with IsFabs (lines ~360-410). Add explicit handling when RHS is +0.0 for ordered/unsigned comparisons:
- For fabs(x) ogt +0.0: return {Src, ~fcZero & ~fcNan, fcZero | fcNan}.
- For fabs(x) oge +0.0: true for any non-NaN, so return {Src, ~fcNan, fcNan}.
- For fabs(x) olt +0.0: false (no magnitude less than zero), so return {Src, fcNone, fcAllFlags}.
- For fabs(x) ole +0.0: true exactly for zeros (non-NaN zeros), so return {Src, fcZero, ~fcZero | fcNan}.
- For unordered variants, invert appropriately.
This ensures the true-branch mask includes negative classes for ogt, preventing ValueTracking from concluding non-negativity.

Concrete change (at lines 360-410): inside the "else if (IsPositiveRHS)" block, after computing ClassesGE/ClassesLE and before applying inverse_fabs, insert a special-case branch:
  if (IsFabs && RHSClass == fcPosZero) {
    switch (Pred) {
    case FCmpInst::FCMP_OGT:
      return {Src, ~fcZero & ~fcNan, fcZero | fcNan};
    case FCmpInst::FCMP_OGE:
      return {Src, ~fcNan, fcNan};
    case FCmpInst::FCMP_OLT:
      return {Src, fcNone, fcAllFlags};
    case FCmpInst::FCMP_OLE:
      return {Src, fcZero, ~fcZero | fcNan};
    case FCmpInst::FCMP_UGT:
      // unordered greater-than: true for non-zero or NaN
      return {Src, (~fcZero) , fcZero};
    case FCmpInst::FCMP_UGE:
      // unordered greater-equal: true for non-NaN or NaN (always true)
      return {Src, fcAllFlags, fcNone};
    case FCmpInst::FCMP_ULT:
      // unordered less-than: true for NaN only
      return {Src, fcNan, ~fcNan};
    case FCmpInst::FCMP_ULE:
      // unordered less-equal: true for zero or NaN
      return {Src, fcZero | fcNan, ~(fcZero | fcNan)};
    default:
      break;
    }
  }
Then proceed with existing logic for other RHS.

Note: The unordered cases above follow the semantics of unordered predicates including NaN. If preferred, they can be derived by inverting the ordered cases per existing code style.

5. Conclusion:
By correcting the class-mask deduction for "fcmp ogt fabs(x), +0.0", ValueTracking will no longer incorrectly assert that the select's true branch is non-negative. Consequently, computeKnownFPSignBit(%sel) will be indeterminate (or true for some paths), preventing InstSimplify from removing the final fabs. This fixes the miscompile demonstrated by the reproducer and aligns class reasoning with the semantics of fabs and ordered comparisons with zero.

